interview questions
1.Q: Can EBS be shared across AZ? When do you use EFS?

"EBS is AZ locked — it can only attach to nodes in the same AZ. For StatefulSet like MySQL, each pod gets its own EBS in its own AZ via volumeClaimTemplates — they don't share storage, they replicate data via MySQL replication over network. EFS is used when multiple pods across different AZs need to read and write the same files — like shared media uploads, ML models, or config files. EFS uses ReadWriteMany access mode while EBS uses ReadWriteOnce. In production EKS, I use EBS for databases and EFS for shared application storage."
